name: "Lucy" Necklace - Cat Skull, Ribs and Vertebrae
description:
This necklace is composed entirely of real bone with brass and pearl beads. The skull, ribs, vertebrae and accent bones are all from the same cat - a beautiful black cat named Lucy. Her owner is a dear friend of mine and she requested that her cat continue on as a work of art after her death. I truly hope I have done justice to Lucy and made her former owner proud.

Please note: the ribs on this necklace are quite fragile and should be handled with care.

name: Turkey Skull Rosary - All Bone
description: This rosary is made from a turkey skull, and each small "bead" is a snake vertebrae. The larger "beads" are neck bones.

name: Turkey Talon Necklace
description:
This necklace is currently my favorite, and I truly hate to part with it. It is composed of turkey phalanges and talons.

This necklace measures approximately 16” around and falls 5” in the center.

name: Syringe Necklace
description: This necklace is composed of black rubber tubing and glass syringes filled with absinthe green beads. It is extremely long and not exactly very quiet while walking. Then again - if you're looking for something subtle, you're probably not looking here. ;)

name: Twin Necklace & Earrings - Green
description:
This necklace and earring set has a bit of sweet story, really. Normally, all the pieces I do are one of a kind, but this has a twin set as well - but in purple.

The reason I chose to make a twin set is because the bones are from a pair of lambs. They were siblings, born at the same time, but one got sick after its birth. It went off on its own to die, but the other followed along and they died together as well. The bones of both lambs have been mixed together to create two companion pieces - The Twins - and their bones shall remain together forever.

name: Twin Necklace & Earrings - Purple
description:
This necklace and earring set has a bit of sweet story, really. Normally, all the pieces I do are one of a kind, but this has a twin set as well - but in green.

The reason I chose to make a twin set is because the bones are from a pair of lambs. They were siblings, born at the same time, but one got sick after its birth. It went off on its own to die, but the other followed along and they died together as well. The bones of both lambs have been mixed together to create two companion pieces - The Twins - and their bones shall remain together forever.

name: Turkey Skull Trio with Beading
description: This necklace is composed of three turkey skulls - each dipped in black enamel and resin. There are multiple falls of black and red beading. Quite the statement piece.

name: Snake Vertebrae Choker
description: This necklace is composed of snake vertebrae and a single vertebrae centerpiece from a raccoon (as I recall, but I may be incorrect on this point).

name: Mink Skull and Canine Scapula Necklace
description: This necklace is composed of a mink skull and the scapula of a dog.

name: Python and Peacock Vertebrae Necklace
description: This necklace is made from ball python vertebrae and peacock neck bones.

name: Duck Mandible Necklace
description: This dramatic statement necklace is composed of duck mandibles, vintage ribbed brass beads and vintage brass capped rhinestones.

name: Armadillo Tail Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed from the tail sections of an armadillo with the keratin sheaths still intact. The accent beading is a mixture of hematite and magnetic beads.

This necklace measures 21.5" around. The largest tail section measures 1.25" x 1", and the smallest measures .5" x .425".

name: Large Raccoon Skull and Mink Femur Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of a large raccoon skull, as well as tibias, femurs and vertebrae of a mink. It has definitely been my most visible necklace, being used for multiple photo shoots (including one with Adam Curry of MTV) and was also worn by Stephen Moser to the Austin Fashion Awards.

This necklace measures approximately 18.5” around and the raccoon skull measures approximately 3” x 5” x 2”.

name: Ornate Mink Skull and Snake Vertebrae Necklace
description:
This ornate necklace is composed of concho snake and California king snake vertebrae and a single mink skull, all surrounded by beautiful hand-scrolled and wrapped brass wire.

This necklace measures approximately 16.5” around and the scrollwork/skull portion measures approximately 7.5” x 6.5”.

name: Coyote Vertebrae Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of sun-bleached coyote vertebrae. It is certainly one of my favorites, and falls beautifully to accent a low cut dress.

This necklace measures approximately 17” around, and falls 6.5” down in the center.

name: Trio of Bone Crosses Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of bones from various creatures, fashioned into the shape of three crosses. The draped chain is antique pot metal, and each link is stamped with a cross on both sides. There are a few accent crosses made of obsidian and silver as well.

This necklace measures approximately 22” around, and falls 4.5” in the middle. The crosses measures approximately 4” x 2.5”.

name: Pigeon Tibiotarsus Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of pigeon tibiotarsus bones (leg bones). It is worth noting that this is a very fragile piece and should be worn and handled with care.

The necklace measures approximately 21.5” around.

name: Mink Skull Necklace with Beading
description:
This exquisitely beaded necklace has a mink skull centerpiece, flanked by red, black and silver beading. The mink skull has been coated in black enamel, its teeth painted red, and then the entire skull has been coated in resin.

The necklace measures approximately 20" around, and the mink skull measures approximately 1.5” x 2.25”.

name: Vintage Glass Bubble Necklace Filled with Bones
description:
This necklace is made of vintage glass bubbles with brass caps. Each bubble is filled with tiny ribs, phalanges and other small bones.

This necklace measures 17.5" around. The larger glass bubbles are .825" diameter and the smaller bubbles are .6875" diameter.

name: California King Snake Ribcage Necklace
description:
This dramatic necklace was fashioned to resemble an additional ribcage. It is fashioned from California king snake vertebrae, and the centerpieces are made of jewelry clay, modeled after the top view of vertebrae of a concho snake. The entirety of the frame is hand-spun in antique brass wire.

This necklace measures approximately 15” around the neck. This chest plate measures 8.5” x 10” x 1.75”.

name: Mink Skull and Snake Vertebrae Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of snake vertebrae on hand-scrolled brass wire and a mink skull centerpiece.

It measures approximately 20" around, and the mink skull measures 2.5" x 1.5".

name: Wishbone and Carved Skull Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of brass filigree and brass rings. The wishbone centerpiece is from a foul and the skull is carved from real bone. The cap of the skull is carved of a slightly lighter bone. (As larger bones are hollow, a second piece is required to complete the top of the skull.)

This necklace measures 20" around, and the wishbone measures 3.625" x 2.25". The skull measures 1" x .75".

name: Mice Skulls Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of six mouse skulls, ribbed brass beads and brass drops. Each skull has been dipped in black enamel, then coated in resin.

The necklace measures approximately 17.5" around, and the mouse skulls measure approximately 1.5" x .75".

name: Carved Skull and Rattlesnake Vertebrae Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of rattlesnake bones and antique ribbed brass beads. The skull centerpiece is carved from real ox bone.

The necklace measures approximately 19" around, and the skull measures 1" x .75"

name: Canine Phalanges Necklace
description:
This necklace is composed of coyote phalanges and large, black, heart-shaped beads.

The necklace measures approximately 15.5” around.

name: Necklace with Vial of Cat Claws
description:
This necklace features a vintage watchmaker's vial containing cat claws. The outside of the vial has the abbreviation "ETA 1080" printed in pencil. The vial is securely sealed so the bones will not fall out.

This necklace measures 18.5” long, and the vial measures 1.75" x .75".

name: Necklace with Vial of Bones
description:
This necklace features a vintage watchmaker's vial containing bird and cat bones. The outside of the vial has the abbreviation "FF189" printed in pencil. The vial is securely sealed so the bones will not fall out.

This necklace measures 18.5” long, and the vial measures 1.75" x .75".

name: Wood and Stone Tribal Necklace
description: This necklace is made from real pieces of wood and beads carved from black lava rock. There are also smaller black wood bead accents.

name: Vintage Brass Rhinestone Necklace
description: I adore this necklace. Simple beauty. It is made from an antique chain and antique banded rhinestones. Very Snow White and the Huntsman or Game of Thrones.

name: Steampunk Pocketwatch Necklace #2
description: Necklace made from a pocket watch mechanism and several gears. Non-kinetic.

name: Cat Vertebrae Ring - Lucy
description: This vertebrae came from a very special cat named "Lucy." She belonged to a dear friend of mine who wanted her to be immortalized after death, and you can see many pieces created from her gift in the store. I am eternally grateful for such a selfless gift and the trust implicit in it.

name: Black German Shepherd Vertebrae Ring
description: This ring is composed of a German Shepherd vertebrae and a fully adjustable brass toned coil ring. It measures 1" x 1.5" x 1.5".

name: Unknown Vertebrae Ring
description: Unfortunately, I can't recall the critter this vertebrae came from. This makes me hang my head in shame, and I apologize. It measures 1.25" x 1.75" x 1.25".

name: Porcupine Vertebrae Ring #1
description: This ring is composed of a porcupine vertebrae and a fully adjustable brass coil ring base. It measures 1" x 1.5" x .825".

name: German Shepherd Vertebrae Ring
description: This ring is composed of a vertebrae from a German Shepherd and a fully adjustable coiled brass band. It measures 1.5" x 2" x1.5".

name: Snake Vertebrae Bracelet with Brass Beads
description: This bracelet is composed of snake vertebrae with brass bead accents. It features a handmade hook and eye clasp.

name: Snake Vertebrae Bracelet with Gunmetal Beads
description: This bracelet is composed of snake vertebrae and gunmetal-toned beading. It features a handmade hook and eye clasp.

name: Rattlesnake Vertebrae Earrings
description: These earrings are composed of rattlesnake vertebrae and have dark antiqued brass drops hanging at their center.

name: Porcupine Humerus Hair Clip
description: This hair clip is composed of a humerus bone of a porcupine. It measures 3.25" x 1".

name: Butterfly Sculpture Made from Fish Bones
description: This small butterfly sculpture is made entirely of the bones from a redfish.

name: Bird Sculpture Made from Fish Bones
description: This small sculpture is made of the bones from a redfish and a very tiny skull of a blue grosbeak bird.
